adjective.description: Relating to or denoting the final Paleolithic culture in Europe, following the Solutrean and dated to about 17,000–11,500 years ago. It is characterized by a range of bone and horn tools, and by highly developed cave art.

origin: Late 19th century: from French Magdalénien from La Madeleine, a site of this culture in the Dordogne, France.
